Police spokesperson Moatshe Ngoepe says the motive behind the killing is still unknown. JOHANNESBURG A 25-year-old man has been assaulted and burnt to ashes by members of the community of Mbilwi in Limpopo.Police spokesperson Moatshe Ngoepe says the motive behind the killing is still unknown and has appealed to the community to come forward with any information.Ngoepe says communities may conduct citizen arrests- but should handover the suspects to the police. Police are looking for a group of people who burnt the man. The deceased is till unknown. 